body:
Become a Blacksmith in Minecraft.


### Implemented Features

- Adds Copper, Tin, Bronze, Platinum, Titanium, Cobalt, Mithril and Orichalcum;

- Adds Flint and Bone Tools;

- Added Hammer, for now is just an expensive Pickaxe;



### Planning Features (Not Implemented Yet):

- Adds Clay and Porcelain buckets;

- Put clay into a chest-like pattern in crafting table to create a Hammer Cast;

- Put the cast into the furnace and craft it with a metal block to create a Hammer;

- Use a Hammer to create Ore Dusts. Hammers can't crush metals that are harder than itself;

- Use clay to create pots to store liquids and casts to forge tools.

- Add Mithrill Shrines in Overworld, Aurimite Forges in the Nether and Orichalcum Veins in the End.

- Add Blacksmith Forge to smelt Metals;

- Add Blacksmith Anvil to change Tools;

- Add Sockets to your weapon and transfer magic gems between them;

- Special Alloys combining different metals;
